content:
How can I determine the ideal markup percentage for my Chinese restaurant's menu items based on the cost of ingredients, overhead expenses, and desired profit margin using [JSON data] format? Also, can you provide the calculated prices for the following dishes on my menu: Kung Pao Chicken, Beef Chow Mein, Vegetable Fried Rice, Egg Drop Soup, and Steamed Dumplings? The [JSON data] is as follows:
{
   "menu_items":[
      {
         "name":"Kung Pao Chicken",
         "ingredient_cost":2.50,
         "overhead_expenses":1.50
      },
      {
         "name":"Beef Chow Mein",
         "ingredient_cost":3.00,
         "overhead_expenses":1.75
      },
      {
         "name":"Vegetable Fried Rice",
         "ingredient_cost":1.75,
         "overhead_expenses":1.25
      },
      {
         "name":"Egg Drop Soup",
         "ingredient_cost":1.25,
         "overhead_expenses":1.00
      },
      {
         "name":"Steamed Dumplings",
         "ingredient_cost":2.00,
         "overhead_expenses":1.50
      }
   ],
   "desired_profit_margin":0.30
}
